Design correction — Yes/No variable type (flagged by power user):
The Yes/No variable type in Section 4.3 needs to be corrected. Yes/No implies a simple true/false abstraction but HA booleans only apply to actual HA boolean helpers. Devices report their own native states — on/off, open/closed, detected/clear, active/inactive — not yes/no.
Decision: Keep Yes/No as a variable type for actual HA boolean helpers only. For device states, the capability-driven wizard fetches and displays the real native values from HA — whatever HA reports for that specific device. No translation layer, no abstraction. The wizard already does this correctly by design. The variable type table in Section 4.3 should be updated to clarify this distinction, and any UI text that implies Yes/No covers device on/off states should be corrected.
When updating DESIGN.md for this, also check Section 6.4 conditions and Section 9 operators to make sure no operator language assumes yes/no as a device state.
